JOHANNESBURG - Gupta-owned Oakbay Investments says Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan's court application against it, is riddled with legal errors. The family claims the minister is using his position to diminish Oakbay and damage its businesses.Gordhan has accused the Guptas of running a highly-organised campaign against him and Treasury.READ: Guptas accuse Gordhan of having 'reverse victim syndrome'In court papers filed on Monday, the minister denies the family s claims he's driving a politically-motivated plan.The Guptas have also rubbished a Financial Intelligence Centre certificate that identifies 72 suspicious transactions of the family businesses.The family blames the minister for the decision by four major banks to cut ties with their companies.Gordhan says there's no evidence of this and stresses his job is to protect Treasury from political influence.eNCA